definition.value: A terminal acetylenic compound that is butane carrying a triple bond at position 1.
A xylonic acid with D configuration.
The open-chain form of D-fructose.
A vinca alkaloid with a norvinblastine skeleton.
A nitrogen oxoacid of formula HNO3 in which the nitrogen atom is bonded to a hydroxy group and by equivalent bonds to the remaining two oxygen atoms.
The inorganic group -P(=O)OH2.
A C-nitro compound with formula C6H(6-n)(NO2)n (n can be from 1 up to 6, but is usually 1, 2 or 3). A closed class.

A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (2S,3R)- and (2R,3S)-epoxiconazole. A broad-spectrum fungicide for control of diseases caused by Ascomycetes, Basidiomycetes and Deuteromycetes. Epoxiconazole is moderately toxic to birds, honeybees, earthworms and most aquatic organisms.
A trinitrobenzene in which each of the nitro groups is meta- to the other two.
An amino acid derivative that is any conjugate between a nucleotide and an amino acid.
Any member of the class of pyrimidine ribonucleosides in which the pyrimidine moiety consists of 2-amino-4-hydroxypyrimidine or its derivatives.
Anthracyclines are polyketides that have a tetrahydronaphthacenedione ring structure attached by a glycosidic linkage to the amino sugar daunosamine.
An olefin that contains more than one carbon-carbon double bond.
A trivalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of three protons from silicic acid.
A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of two protons from silicic acid.
A monovalent inorganic anion that consists of silicic acid in which one of the four OH groups has been deprotonated.
Octaketides are polyketide compounds that are synthesized from eight ketide units. They are derivatives of a 16-carbon skeleton.
Nonaketides are polyketide compounds that are synthesized from nine ketide units. They are derivatives of a 18-carbon skeleton.
Decaketides are polyketide compounds that are synthesized from ten ketide units. They are derivatives of a 20-carbon skeleton.
A class of Streptomyces aromatic polyketide antibiotics.
Polyketides produced by Actinomycetes which have structures based on the benz[a]anthracene ring system, several of which bear hydrolysable sugars.
An alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is heptane substituted at positions 1 and 7 by carboxy groups.
A polyketide based on a tetracene ring structure.
